Absolutely low life place. Lies lies lies. That's all the serve you. The women go in for free but the men pay $280 for cover/drinks. But only when you reach the bar u realize its only one drink! You can't order anything els.

We were physically assaulted by the manager at Centralz club in LKF himself as we attempted to re enter the club, I myself was questioned which county I was from, when they found out that I wasnt from hong kong, I was pushed off the staircase and was admitted to the hospital thereafter for a surgery on my lower back injury from said incident. Highly not recommended.

Didn’t get in even though I showed two if cards!! Have never met such rude guards, I am over 18 and didn’t get in, an all the reason they gave me was that I didn’t bring my passport even though all my friends got in with the same type of ID I had. The staff was so rude, and I heard this was one of the best pubs in HK. Never returning.

result.adr_address: 30-32 D'Aguilar St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: California Tower

reviews.text: Big tower. Good views on a clear night. Quite expensive but you’d expect that at the top!
Gorgeous rooftop bar, Ce La Vie on the very top floor! Beautiful views of Hong Kong.

Good selection of restaurants from the bottom floor to the top. Or if you want to get your sweat on then I'd highly recommend signing up for the Pure gym - chances are this is the closest one to those working in central. Top floors have pretty great views, particularly towards the south.
There's this bar located at the rooftop called Cest La Vie. A really nice bar to chill at! Love it!
Pure Fitness at California tower is the best gym in town!
